description:
Proper Japanese Title: 母の… (Haha no... Te...)

Mero and her two friends tell tales of their own brushes with zombies. Ichie tells of the creature that the art teacher keeps; Miko relates the story of an awful smell that led her to a house of horror. Mero's story, however, trumps them both.
name: Mother's... Hand...

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 強い…思い… (Tsuyoi... Omoi...)

While being held hostage inside the Sanka mansion, Chihiro meets Aria. She discloses that she is Rea's stepmother, and relates how she came to be married to Dan'ichiro. In the course of her tale, more about Dan'ichiro's past is also revealed to Chihiro.
name: Strong... Affections

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 特別…なんかじゃ…ない… (Tokubetsu... Nanka ja... nai...)

Rea arrives home just as Dan'ichiro shows Chihiro into the fencing hall, where he is determined to settle things between them. Though detained by the maid staff, Rea is able to elude them, and rushes to save Chihiro, but is startled by what she finds.
name: It's... Nothing... Special...

description:
Proper Japanese Title: あの瞬間…俺は… (Ano Shunkan... Ore wa...)

Chihiro begins to have second thoughts about his duty in looking after Rea's welfare, and how little he can do for her. When plans to watch a fireworks show that Rea has her heart set on seeing fall through, the group comes up with an alternative.
name: At That Moment... I...

description:
Proper Japanese Title: なないろ導花線 (Nanairo Shirube Hanasen)

Sheltered Nai is on a journey in search of Karoku, a man who abruptly disappeared from his life. All he has to go on is Karoku's bracelet, a form of ID for members of Circus - a government agency made up of men and women with supernatural powers.
name: Rainbow Colored Flower Fuse

description:
Proper Japanese Title: フォーチュンキャット (Fōchun Kyatto)

Now that Nai knows Karoku's bracelet has something to do with Circus, he goes in search of answers, but he finds that his earlier brush with trouble is far from over.
name: Fortune Cat

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 幻ピクニック (Maboroshi Pikunikku)

While under Circus's protection, a curious fact comes to light regarding Nai's true identity. With that clue in hand, Nai, Gareki, and several members of Circus pay a visit to where they believe Nai came from.
name: Fantasy Picnic

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 宵待燕 (Yoima Tsubame)

After their trip to Rainbow Forest, Gareki asks to drop by Karasuna, where they run into an old acquaintance of his. From this enounter, Nai and Yogi learn more about Gareki's past.
name: Evening Swallow

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ピエロの処方箋 (Piero no Shohōsen)

Yotaka has become a Varuga and Yogi fights him, telling Gareki and Nai to get back to Karasuna on their own. But Gareki feels very conflicted about his past with Yotaka and Tsubame, and what has happened to them now.
name: Clown Prescription

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 朝陽の翼 (Asahi no Tsubasa)

With Yotaka gone, Gareki and Tsubame are left to pick up the pieces and make sense of what has happened.
name: Wings of Morning Light

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 「マーメイドの溜息」と三人の騎士 (Māmeido no Tameki to Sannin no Kishi)

Team Two is helping Team One put on their Circus parade and show, and Yogi gets Nai and Gareki to join the parade in an effort to cheer up Gareki. But a malfunctioning Team One rabbit throws a wrench into their festivities.
name: The Mermaid's Sigh and the Three Knights

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 白銀の匣 (Shirogane no Kushige)

Yogi and Tsukumo are sent on a mission to Rinole, the City of Ice, to follow-up an investigation started by Team One. Nai and Gareki are sent along with them, and the four of them find more than they bargained for.
name: Silvery Box

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 蒼い薔薇 (Aoi Bara)

Yogi going berserk sends the bad guys running, but when Nai senses that something is wrong with him, Tsukumo turns back alone, only to run into trouble herself.
name: Blue Rose

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 猛獣使の泪 (Mōjū-shi no Namida)

With Yogi and Tsukumo out of commission, Nai and Gareki are given into the care of Airship One. The team dynamic is a little different, but the two of them still go on a mission with them, where Gareki learns more about their special powers.
name: Tears of the Wild Beast Tamer

description:
Proper Japanese Title: アイスクリームパレード (Aisukurīmuparēdo)

Hirato and Tsukumo take a meeting with the CEO of the Lindain Group in Vantnum while the rest of the gang gets the day off. The CEO has disturbing news, but a boy they run into in the city has even more intriguing information.
name: Ice Cream Parade

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ニジの約束 (Niji no Yakusoku)

Nai is determined to go to the Misty Mansion, a Kafka facility, in order to rescue Karoku. And Circus decides to use this as an excuse to raid the facility.
name: The Niji's Promise

description:
Proper Japanese Title: カーニヴァル (Kānivuaru)

As Nai and Gareki make their way towards the mysterious rainbow to see if Karoku is there, the rest of Circus work to wrap up what they can of the raid on the Kafka facility.
name: Karneval
Love Is a Many Splintered Thing
It's a Bird, It's Insane, It's Dale!
When You Fish Upon a Star

description:
Proper Japanese Title: はい、魔装少女です (Hai, Ma Sou Shoujo Desu)

Ayumu is a boy with a problem. He's dead. Well, actually he's a zombie, and he's about to be chopped in half by a magical girl in pink dress with a matching chainsaw. Some guys just can't catch a break.
name: Yes, I'm A Magical Garment Girl

description:
Proper Japanese Title: いえ、吸血忍者です (Ie, Kyuuketsu Ninja Desu)

Dinner time is rudely interrupted by a mysterious female with an insatiable hunger for miso soup. Apparently, there is a war raging in the village of ninjas, and the curvy newcomer could use Eu's help.
name: No, It's A Vampire Ninja

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 髪型はツインテールに (Sou , Kamigata wa Tsuinteuru ni)

While Ayumu goes bowling with a friend from school, his three lovely roommates spend the afternoon playing twister and fighting over the last package of pudding.
name: Yes, Hair In Pigtails

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ちょ、俺輝いてる？ (Cho ,Ore Kagayaiteru ?)

When a talking Doberman shows up at the front door instead of the pizza man, Ayumu learns the tragic secret behind Eu's powers. Oh yeah, there's also a whale of a demon that needs to be put down!
name: Whoa, Am I Glowing?

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ええ、京豆腐どすえ (Ee ,Kyou Toufu Dosue)

Ayumu's romantic rendezvous takes a deadly turn when his dream girl turns out to be a demonic serial killer. It's a good thing zombie boy travels with a vampire ninja and an armor-clad necromancer! Let's get ready to rumble!
name: Yeah, That's Kyoto Tofu

description:
Proper Japanese Title: そう、私は死を呼ぶもの (Sou ,Watashi wa shi wo Yobu Mono)

Eu, the most powerful necromancer in existence, slips into a pretty pink dress and picks up the most darling little chainsaw as she prepares to go all magical girl on a pesky demon with a plethora of lives!
name: Yes, I Summon Death

description:
Proper Japanese Title: おい、お前どこ中だよ？ (Oi ,Omae Doko Chuu Dayo ?)

Ayumu's exams are interrupted by a rampaging demon-horse and the arrival of a killer-soup wielding vampire ninja! If the poor boy can survive his latest adventure, he may find a mate for life!
name: Hey, Which Middle School Are You At?

description:
Proper Japanese Title: えへ、学園妻です (Ehe ,Gakuen Tsuma Desu)

Yuki must learn to like her new husband, Haruna can't decide whether she wants to kiss - or kill - Ayumu, and the Necromancer disappears while no one is looking!
name: Heh, I'm A Schoolyard Wife

description:
Proper Japanese Title: はい、脱ぐと凄いんです (Hai ,Nugu to Sugoin Desu)

A mysterious madman from Eu's past terrorizes her new friends. Will the necromancer give in to his demands, or will she stubbornly watch Ayumu and the others meet their untimely ends?
name: Yes, When I Strip Down, You'll Be Amazed

description:
Proper Japanese Title: いえ、それは爆発します (Ie ,Sore wa Bakuhatsu Shimasu)

Ayumu, Haruna, and Sera desperately search for Eu, but an evil zombie from the necromancer's past is willing to kill to keep her by his undead side.
name: No, That Will Explode

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ああ、オレの所にいろ！ (Aa ,Ore no Tokoro ni Iru !)

In the wake of Eu's abduction, Ayumu finds himself trapped in a bizarre nightmare, and only Haruna has the power wake him. Meanwhile, Sera and her fellow vampires attempt to close the gates of the underworld once and for all.
name: Yeah, You Stay With Me!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: はい、まだ続きます (Hai ,Mada Tsuzukimasu)

The fighting is all finished, but the action is just beginning to heat up! Haruna wins a special trip to the pool, and we all know what that means: swimsuits!
name: Yes, There's Still More

description:
Proper Japanese Title: えぇ,これが最終回ですか? (Ee, Kore ga Saishuukai Desuka?)

Haruna throws a carnival where Eu is the prize. Later, Sera tries her hand at cooking, and Ayumu is repeatedly probed in a very uncomfortable area!

Note: Unofficial episode/oav that came packaged with the limited edition volume 8 of the light novel.
name: Eh? This Is The Final Episode?

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ?

Ayumu tries to keep the peace as Haruna scours the local pool for signs of a sea monster. Later, the necromancer's birthday celebration is disrupted by a demonic void.

Note: Unofficial episode/oav that came packaged with the limited edition volume 10 of the light novel.
name: Yes, Thank You For This Encore

description:
Proper Japanese Title: はい、今再びの魔装変身！ (Hai, Ima Futatabi Masou Henshin!)

After an encounter with a mysterious drunk girl, Ayumu is forced to battle a Megalo in front of the entire school, shocking his schoolmates and damaging a very special chainsaw.
name: Yes, I'm Now Making A Magical Transformation Again!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 嗚呼、さようなら俺 (Aa, Sayonara Ore)

Ayumu's hiking date with Yuki is interrupted by a swarm of angry bees and a very large bear. Back at school, the zombie is shocked to learn of his newfound celebrity status!
name: Aah, Farewell To Me

description:
Proper Japanese Title: Yo！それは You！ 情！ (Yo! Sore wa You! Jou!)

Haruna tries valiantly to repair her magic chainsaw, but she gets sidetracked after agreeing to help Yuki learn a deadly curse dance!
name: Yo! That's Some Friendly You-nity!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: いや、帰れご主人様 (Iya, Kaere Goshujin-sama)

Orito hopes to cure Ayumu of his cross-dressing habit by treating him to dinner at a maid café! Hijinks ensue when the maids turn out to be the zombie's roommates!
name: No, Get Lost, Good Sir

description:
Proper Japanese Title: はい、毎年流行ってます (Hai, Mainen Hayattemasu)

When Sera goes away for the weekend, Eu gets sick, and Ayumu and Haruna must work together to nurse the necromancer back to health.
name: Yes, It Goes Around Every Year

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ちゃうねん、勝てててん (Chaunen, Kateteten)

Ayumu receives a ring from a mysterious blood-spewing man, and Haruna is overjoyed at the return of her chainsaw - and her magic powers!
name: No Way, We Were Winning!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: うん、先生が最強だよ！ (Un, Sensei ga Saikyou Dayo!)

Haruna's magic gadget leads to the loss of her voice, and Ayumu's adorable little drinking buddy turns out to be a very powerful nightmare!
name: Mm-hmm, Teacher Is the Greatest!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: フー、京子ちゃん合コンだゼッ! (FUU, Kyouko-chan wa GOUKON da ZE-!)

Ayumu is forced to throw a mixer for his own murderer if he wants to unlock the secret to defeating Chris - and return Haruna to her former power!
name: Whoo, A Mixer With Kyoko!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ああ、マイダーリンはロクデナシ (Aa, MAI DAARIN wa ROKU DE NASHI)

Ayumu continues his quest to defeat Chris by helping the most powerful warrior from the underworld finish drawing her manga. If he doesn't finish fast, however, he'll be late for Saras' concert!
name: Ah, My Darling Is A Ne'er-do-well

description:
Proper Japanese Title: だけど、それがいい (Dakedo, Sore ga Ii)

When Ayumu is robbed of his memories, the necromancer becomes a magical girl and goes to war with the zombie!
name: Still, That's Okay

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ?

Haruna accidentally sells a philosopher's stone, Ayumu becomes temporarily invisible, and a bevy of scantily clad beauties are about to be unwittingly gazed upon by the eyes of a zombie!

Note: Unofficial episode/oav that came packaged with the limited edition volume 6 of the manga.
name: Yes, This Suits Me Just Fine

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ホントのエース (Hontō no Esu)

Most guys can’t wait for the start of baseball season. But not Mihashi. For this young pitcher, the crack of the bat is the sound of yet another failure.
name: The Real Ace

description:
Proper Japanese Title: キャッチャーの役割 (Kyāchā no Yakuwari)

Mihashi wants to be an ace, but he’s got no confidence. That’s where Abe comes in. Every pitcher needs a good catcher, and Mihashi’s new teammate is magic behind the plate.
name: The Catcher's Role

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 練習試合 (Renshū Shiai)

Mihashi still doubts himself, and Abe always has to be the boss. If the Nishiura nine want to beat Mihashi’s old team, pitcher and catcher must learn to trust each other.
name: The Practice Match

description:
Proper Japanese Title: プレイ (Purei)

Mihashi takes the mound, but he’s shaking in his stirrups. His old teammates weren’t his biggest fans, and they can’t wait to take some vicious cuts against him.
name: The Play

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 手を抜くな (Te wo Mekuna)

The game is scoreless through three innings, and Mihashi’s locked in a pitcher’s duel with his old backup. As usual, Abe is at the center of all the action.
name: Don't Cut Corners

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 投手の条件 (Tōshu no Jyōken)

Mihashi’s mowing down batters until an error by the left fielder gives his old team new life. With their lead cut in half, the Nishiura players start to tense up.
name: Requirements for Pitchers

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 野球したい (Yakyū Shitai)

Abe and Mihashi get back on the same page, but not before giving up the lead. As the game enters the final innings, Mihashi must trust his teammates.
name: I Want to Play Baseball!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: スゴイ投手? (Sugoi Tōshu)

Mihashi should be fired up about beating his old team, but instead he's obsessing over Haruna - the star pitcher at Abe's old school.
name: An Amazing Pitcher

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 過去 (Kako)

When the Nishiura nine attend a tournament, Mihashi gets a chance to see Abe's old pitcher light up the radar gun.
name: The Past

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ちゃくちゃくと (Chaku chaku To)

When Coach Momoe and Abe discuss the need for a second pitcher, Mihashi sees his dreams - and his special day - going up in flames.
name: Bit by Bit

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 夏がはじまる (Natsu ga Hajimaru)

Team Nishiura is stoked about playing in the prestigious summer tournament, but there's a catch - they have to play Tosei, the defending champs, in the first round.
name: The Summer Starts

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 応援団 (Ōendan)

They may be facing the toughest game of their lives, but the Nishiura nine aren't gonna roll over and die. This team has plenty of fight left in it!
name: The Cheering Squad

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 夏大開始 (Natsutai Kaishi)

The summer baseball tournament is about to begin, and the players are itching to get on the field. Now, if only Mihashi can just stay cool.
name: The Summer Tournament Begins

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 挑め! (Idome!)

Play ball! The game starts with a surprise as Nishiura gets the lead-off hitter on base against their talented opponents.
name: Challenge

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 先取点 (Senshuten)

A Nishiura rally in the second puts runners in scoring position, but it means Mihashi's gonna have to step into the batter's box - the one place Abe can't help him.
name: The First Run of the Game

description:
Proper Japanese Title: あなどるな (Anadoruna)

Despite a base-running blunder, Nishiura draws first blood! Staked to a one run lead, Mihashi just has to keep the other team in check.
name: Don't Underestimate

description:
Proper Japanese Title: サードランナー (Sādo Rannā)

A close game quickly becomes a chess match with both coaches anticipating the other's next move. Mihashi's hitting his spots, but the opposing team's strategy leads to crowded base paths.
name: The Third Runner

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 追加点 (Tsuikaden)

Tosei put some serious pressure on Mihashi in the bottom of the fourth, but stingy defense and Tajima's instincts help them escape without allowing a run.
name: Another Score

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 桐青の実力 (Tōsei no Jitsuryoku)

He's pitching a good game, but Mihashi's starting to wear down. Tajima and Abe have noticed he's not quite right, and Tosei's getting closer to figuring out his pitches.
name: Tosei's Real Power

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 逆転 (Gyakuten)

When a pitcher doesn't have great stuff, he has to be crafty. But even with Abe's game plan, the momentum shifts to Tosei in the bottom of the seventh.
name: Turning the Tables

description:
Proper Japanese Title: もう一点 (Mō Itten)

Tosei rallies to take the lead, but Tajima comes to the plate determined to put his team back on top.
name: One More Run

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 防げ (Fusege!)

Tied 3-3 in the last of the eighth, Tosei will do anything to avoid losing to a bunch of first years - even they have to bunt their way home.
name: Defense!

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ゲンミツに (Genmitsu ni)

As the final inning begins, things look bleak for Nishiura. They've fought and clawed and left everything they've got on the field, but Tosei leads by a run.
name: Precisely

description:
Proper Japanese Title: 決着 (Ketchaku)

Heading into the bottom of the ninth, Nishiura clings to a one run lead, and Mihashi and Abe are ready to bring the victory home!
name: The End of the Game

description:
Proper Japanese Title: ひとつ勝って (Hitotsu Katte)

While his teammates celebrate their amazing and unexpected victory, poor Mihashi can only sleep and sleep and sleep some more.
name: After One Win
